{"content": "Given:  \n\\( a_n = (-1)^{n+1}(3n + 2) \\)\n\nWe are to compute:  \n\\( S = a_1 + a_2 + \\dots + a_{100} \\)\n\nLet's analyze the sequence:\n\n**Step 1: Find \\( a_n \\) for odd and even \\( n \\).**\n\n- For **odd \\( n \\)** (\\( n=2k-1 \\)):\n  - \\( (-1)^{n+1} = (-1)^{2k} = 1 \\)\n  - \\( a_{2k-1} = 1 \\times (3(2k-1) + 2) = 3(2k-1) + 2 = 6k - 3 + 2 = 6k - 1 \\)\n\n- For **even \\( n \\)** (\\( n=2k \\)):\n  - \\( (-1)^{n+1} = (-1)^{2k+1} = -1 \\)\n  - \\( a_{2k} = -1 \\times (3(2k) + 2) = -(6k + 2) \\)\n\nSo the sequence is:\n- \\( a_{2k-1} = 6k - 1 \\)\n- \\( a_{2k} = -(6k + 2) \\)\n\n**Step 2: Sum up to \\( n=", "in": 77, "out": 300}